Outgoing Calls

1. Greetings & Introduction

Quick Tip:
Always use the person’s name and your company’s name to make the call more personal and professional.
Adjust your tone to match the formality of the relationship.

--------------------------------------------------

Professional Phrases

- Hi Raj, this is Viren from ABC Corporation. I hope you're doing well today.
- Hello Neha, I’m Rahul with XYZ Inc. I trust everything is going well.
- Good afternoon, Govind. This is Ram calling from Global Solutions. How are you today?

--------------------------------------------------

Casual Phrases

- Hey Raj, it’s Viren from ABC Corp. How’s everything going?
- Hi Neha, Rahul here from XYZ Inc. Just checking in—how’s it going today?
- Hello Govind, Ram from Global Solutions here. Hope your day has been good so far!

2. Stating the Purpose

Quick Tip:
Be clear and concise about the purpose of your call right away to set the tone and keep the conversation focused.

--------------------------------------------------

Professional Phrases

- I'm calling to discuss the upcoming project deadline and to see how we can move forward with it.
- The purpose of my call is to follow up on the recent client feedback and provide you with the latest updates.
- I wanted to speak with you about the new marketing strategy and get your input on the proposed changes.

--------------------------------------------------

Casual Phrases

- Just calling to chat about the project deadline and see what we can do next.
- I wanted to catch up on the client feedback and get your thoughts.
- I'm reaching out to talk about the marketing strategy. Let’s figure out the next steps.

3. Making Requests

Quick Tip:
Be specific about what you need and include a reasonable timeframe to help the recipient prioritize your request.

--------------------------------------------------

Professional Phrases

- Could you please provide me with the updated sales report at your earliest convenience?
- Would you be able to assist with the final review of the proposal by Friday?
- I would appreciate it if you could send over the new budget figures so we can proceed with the planning.

--------------------------------------------------

Casual Phrases

- Could you send me the updated sales report when you get a chance?
- Can you help out with the final review of the proposal by Friday? That would be great!
- Mind sending over the new budget figures? It will help us move forward.

4. Making Appointments

Quick Tip:
Offer specific times for the appointment and be flexible if needed to accommodate the other person’s schedule.

--------------------------------------------------

Professional Phrases

- I'd like to schedule a meeting to discuss the Q4 strategy. Are you available on Tuesday at 10 AM?
- Can we arrange a time to meet next week to go over the project timeline? What works best for you?
- Would it be possible to set up a call for Thursday at 2 PM to review the contract details?

--------------------------------------------------

Casual Phrases

- How about we set up a time to talk about the Q4 strategy? Are you free on Tuesday at 10 AM?
- When is a good time next week to chat about the project timeline? Let me know!
- Can we plan a call for Thursday at 2 PM to go over the contract details? What works for you?

5. Leaving Messages for Someone

Quick Tip:
Leave your name, contact information, and a brief reason for the call.
Be concise and clear about how they can reach you.

--------------------------------------------------

Professional Phrases

- Hi Prijesh, this is Manish from XYZ Solutions. I'm calling regarding the vendor agreement. Please call me back at [number].
- Hello Ravi, this is Aakash. I wanted to discuss the upcoming merger. You can reach me at [number] when you're available.
- Hi Nitin, this is Shubham from Marketing Inc. I was hoping to speak with you about the new campaign. Please get in touch at your convenience.

--------------------------------------------------

Casual Phrases

- Hey Prijesh, Manish from XYZ Solutions here. Just wanted to talk about the vendor agreement. Give me a call back when you can!
- Hi Ravi, Aakash here. I wanted to go over the upcoming merger. Hit me up at [number] when you get a chance.
- Hi Nitin, this is Shubham from Marketing Inc. Got remember to chat about the new campaign? Give me a shout!

